Linux Users for OpenSimulator
1) opensimulator
2) [SIMULATORNAME] (1 to n)

OpenSimulator Directory Tree

1) /srv/opensimulator/[GRIDNAME]/robust/[ROBUSTSERVICE] (0 to n)
2) /srv/opensimulator/[GRIDNAME]/simulators/[SIMULATORNAME] (0 to n)
3) /srv/opensimulator/managementScripts/
4) /var/opensimulator/backups/OARs/[GRIDNAME]/
5) /var/opensimulator/backups/IARs/[GRIDNAME]/
6) /var/opensimulator/backups/databases/[GRIDNAME]/

1) Create a subfolder per service, if needed
2) Create a subfolder per simulator

OpenSimulator Database

1) [GRIDNAME][SERVICENAME] (1 to n*m) (n grids, m services)
2) [GRIDNAME]Estates
3) [GRIDNAME][SIMULATORNAME] (1 to n*m) (n grids, m simulators)

1) It's for the robust services

OpenSimulator Ports

8000 to 8999 TCP: Robust Ports
9000 to 9999 UDP: Regions Ports
9000 to 9999 TCP: Simulators Ports
10000 to 10999 TCP: Remote Admin Ports
11000 to 11999 TCP: REST Console Ports
